label.value: normal phosphorylation of RNA polymerase II C-terminal domain serine 5 residues during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of the serine residue at position 5 within one or more copies of the heptapeptide repeat (YSPTSPS) of the C-terminal domain of RNA polymerase II normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: increased histone H3-K4 methylation at telomere during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the methylation of lysine at position 4 of histone H3 in telomeric regions occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: increased histone H3-K4 methylation at mating type locus during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the methylation of lysine at position 4 of histone H3 at the mating type locus occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: increased histone H3-K9 methylation at telomere during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which methylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 in telomeric regions occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: increased histone H3-K9 methylation at mating type locus during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which methylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 at the mating type locus occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: increased histone H3-K9 methylation at centromere during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which methylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 in centromeric regions occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: sensitive to 1,1-bis(2-aminoethyl)-2-hydroxy-3-oxotriazane

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to 1,1-bis(2-aminoethyl)-2-hydroxy-3-oxotriazane (DETA NONOate). Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of 1,1-bis(2-aminoethyl)-2-hydroxy-3-oxotriazane that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: increased number of double-strand break sites during mitotic S phase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the number of sites of double-strand breaks in DNA is greater than normal during S phase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: Because Rad22 often accumulates at double-strand breaks, consider also annotating to 'increased number of Rad52 foci during vegetative growth' (FYPO:0000972).

label.value: unequal mitotic sister chromatid segregation following normal mitosis

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which mitotic sister chromatid segregation fails to separate chromosomes into two equal masses after the cell has undergone a normal mitotic nuclear division and passed through the subsequent mitotic interphase. Unequal mitotic sister chromatid separation may be complete, with two distinct unequal DNA masses located at or near the ends of an elongated mitotic spindle, or incomplete.

definition.value: This phenotype affects the second round of mitosis to take place after a mutation exerts its effect. For example, if a conditional mutant is shifted to restrictive conditions in G1 or S phase and the first mitosis thereafter is normal, but the second is not (even if cells are returned to permissive conditions), this term is applicable.

label.value: increased chromatin silencing at centromere

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which chromatin silencing at centromeric regions is increased.

definition.value: Chromatin silencing phenotypes may reflect the assembly or maintenance of heterochromatin or CENP-A-containing chromatin. See the GO cellular component terms 'heterochromatin' (GO:0000792) and 'CENP-A containing chromatin' (GO:0061638), and the biological process terms 'heterochromatin organization' (GO:0070828) and 'CENP-A containing chromatin organization' (GO:0061641).

label.value: normal protein localization to centromeric chromatin

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to centromeric chromatin is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased mitotic chromosome arm condensation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mitotic chromosome condensation occurs to a lower extent than normal along the chromosome arms.

label.value: normal protein level in anaphase-promoting complex

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of a protein measured in the anaphase-promoting complex is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased anaphase-promoting complex assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of anaphase-promoting complex assembly is decreased.

label.value: elongated cell during glucose starvation

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a cell becomes elongated, i.e. has a greater length and length:diameter ratio than normal, when the cell is subject to glucose starvation.

definition.value: Note that FYPO uses "glucose starvation" to refer specifically to conditions in which glucose is scarce enough to trigger mating, meiosis, and sporulation. For phenotypes observed in the presence of enough glucose to prevent cells from mating, use a term that specifies "during vegetative growth" plus a condition to indicate low glucose.

label.value: sensitive to canavanine and rapamycin

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to a combination of canavanine and rapamycin. Cells stop growing (and may die) at concentrations of canavanine and rapamycin that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: normal protein localization to chromatin at centromere central core

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at the central core of the centromeric regions is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to heterochromatin at centromere inner repeat

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at the centromere inner repeat regions is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to chromatin at long terminal repeat

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at long terminal repeat regions is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to chromatin at ncRNA gene

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at non-coding RNA (ncRNA) genes is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to chromatin at rRNA gene

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at ribosomal RNA (rRNA) genes is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to chromatin at snRNA gene

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at small nuclear RNA (snRNA) genes is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to chromatin at snoRNA gene

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at small nucleolar RNA (snoRNA) genes is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to chromatin at tRNA gene

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at transfer RNA (tRNA) genes is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: inviable after spore germination, multiple cell divisions, binucleate septated cell

value.value: A phenotype in which a spore germinates to produce a cell that contains two nuclei and one or more septa, and undergoes two or more rounds of cell division, and then dies.

label.value: abolished RNA polymerase II carboxy-terminal domain kinase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which RNA polymerase II carboxy-terminal domain kinase activity is absent.

label.value: decreased level of cytokinesis gene mRNA during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of one or more cytokinesis RNAs measured in a cell is lower than normal (i.e. lower than observed in wild-type cells). Cytokinesis RNAs are transcribed from genes whose products are involved in one or more cytokinetic processes.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription.

label.value: normal DNA binding at PCB

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of DNA binding at a pombe cell cycle box (PCB) by a gene product is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). The relevant gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

label.value: inviable after spore germination, multiple cell divisions, swollen, elongated pear-shaped cell

value.value: A phenotype in which a spore germinates to produce a cell that has a greater length, diameter, and volume than normal, is shaped in the form of a pear, and undergoes two or more rounds of cell division and then dies. In a pear-shaped cell, one end is rounded, while the other resembles an end of a normal rod-shaped cell.

label.value: decreased duration of protein phosphorylation during cellular response to hydroxyurea

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the duration of protein phosphorylation is shorter than normal during a cellular response to hydroxyurea. All phosphorylation may be affected, or only phosphorylation of specific proteins, or even specific sites within specific proteins.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased duration of S-phase DNA damage checkpoint during cellular response to hydroxyurea

value.value: A cell cycle checkpoint phenotype in which the duration of cell cycle arrest or delay due to regulation by the S-phase DNA damage checkpoint is lower than in wild type during a cellular response to hydroxyurea.

label.value: abolished protein localization to chromatin at replication origin

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at replication origins is abolished.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased duration of protein localization to mitotic spindle pole body during anaphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which one or more proteins is localized to the mitotic spindle pole body for a longer time than normal during anaphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal cell cycle arrest in mitotic G1 phase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which progression through the mitotic cell cycle is abnormally arrested during G1 phase. Arrest may either occur under conditions where arrest is not a normal occurrence, or may progress differently from normal under conditions where arrest normally does take place.

definition.value: Use this term for terminal arrest. If arrest is transient, consider using 'increased duration of mitotic cell cycle phase' (FYPO:0001069) or one of its more specific descendants.

label.value: abnormal poly(A) polymerase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of poly(A) polymerase activity (EC name polynucleotide adenylyltransferase activity) is abnormal.

label.value: decreased poly(A) polymerase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of poly(A) polymerase activity (EC name polynucleotide adenylyltransferase activity) is decreased.

label.value: normal poly(U) polymerase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of poly(U) polymerase activity (EC name RNA uridylyltransferase activity) is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: decreased poly(U) RNA binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which an interaction between a protein and a polyuridylated RNA (poly(U)RNA) is decreased. One of the relevant gene products may be encoded by the mutated gene, or both the RNA and protein may be encoded by genes other than the mutated one.

label.value: decreased protein level at silent mating-type cassette

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of a protein found associated with chromatin at the mating type region is lower than normal when the cell is in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: curved elongated vegetative cell

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a vegetatively growing cell is elongated, and is curved along the long axis. In a curved cell, the long axis follows a smooth bend rather than a straight line.

label.value: abnormal Lys63-specific deubiquitinase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of Lys63-specific deubiquitinase activity is abnormal.

label.value: abolished Lys63-specific deubiquitinase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which Lys63-specific deubiquitinase activity is absent.

label.value: decreased Lys63-specific deubiquitinase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of Lys63-specific deubiquitinase activity is decreased.

label.value: normal regulation of mitotic DNA replication initiation

value.value: A regulation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which regulation of mitotic DNA replication initiation is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal rate of mitotic DNA replication elongation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of DNA strand elongation involved in mitotic nuclear DNA replication is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: premature protein localization to chromatin at replication origin

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at replication origins begins earlier than normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal sodium export

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the export of sodium ions out of a cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: abnormal ubiquitin-specific protease activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of ubiquitin-specific protease activity is abnormal.

label.value: decreased ubiquitin-specific protease activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of ubiquitin-specific protease activity is decreased.

label.value: increased ubiquitin-specific protease activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of ubiquitin-specific protease activity is increased.
